<P><H1 align=center>DC141 – ADD/EDIT BANKRUPTCY HISTORY</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>fields shown in 
red are mandatory and must be completed to proceed</FONT>            </P>
<P><H3>Applicant: </H3>Select the applicant who has been 
previously declared bankrupt. If the application is in sole name, the name will 
be pre-completed.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Amount of Debt: </H3>Input the amount of debt 
outstanding.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Monthly Repayment: </H3>Input the amount being paid 
monthly to clear the debt.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Date Declared: </H3>Input the date the applicant was 
officially declared bankrupt by the courts.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Date of Discharge: </H3>Input the date the bankruptcy 
order was officially discharged by the courts.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Other details: </H3>Input any additional details 
required in this box. 
<P></P>
<P><H3>Another: </H3>If there are further bankruptcy orders in 
place, click on the ANOTHER button
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>click OK to return to the previous 
screen.
